@Database GUI.Guide

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "Using The GUI"

  Using the GUI
  =============

  @{" Control GUI        " link CtrlGUI  } All the buttons explained for the control panel
    @{" Control Config     " link ControlConfigWindow}

  @{" Node GUI           " link NodeGUI  } All the buttons explained for the node control window.
    @{" Node Settings      " link NodeSettingsWin}
    @{" Node Information   " link NodeInfoWin }

  @{" Keyboard shortcuts " link KeyboardShortcuts } Keyboard shortcuts

@EndNode

@Node CtrlGUI "Control GUI"

  Control Window GUI
  ==================

  The control window has the following gadgets on it:

  Listview 1     - (Located towards the top left of the window)

                   Lists all the nodes on the bbs, regardless of wether they
                   are open or closed.

                   If you single click a node in the list the status line
                   at the bottom of the window will update to show the
                   current status of the node.  It will also update
                   Listview gadget 2 (to the right of this listview gadget)
                   to show the currently selected information which depends
                   on Cycle Gadget 1

                   If you double click a node and it is closed, the node
                   will start up.

                   If you double click a node and the node is online or
                   ready the node's watch window/screen will open and pop
                   to the front.                                                     *I*

  Start          - Will start the last node clicked on if the node is closed

  Stop           - will stop the last node clicked if the node's status is
                   ready.  It has no effect if a user is on-line.

  Screen         - Will open the watch screen/window and pop it to the front

  Window         - Will open the node's @{" control window " link NodeGUI}

  Config         - Brings up the @{" NodeLocal " link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeLocal.guide/MAIN} config file for the node
                   you last clicked on.  (Uses the @{" BBSGlobal/EditorCMD " link HBBS:docs/configuration/bbsglobal.guide/editorcmd})
                   to decide what program to use to edit the config files)

  Device         - Brings up the @{" Device " link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/Device.guide/MAIN} config file for the node
                   you last clicked on.  (Uses the @{" BBSGlobal/EditorCMD " link HBBS:docs/configuration/bbsglobal.guide/editorcmd})
                   to decide what program to use to edit the config files)

  Cycle Gadget 1 - (located above the Listview gadget 2, which is the second
                    listview gadget from the left of the window)

                  You can select one of the following

                    Last Callers
                    Last Downloads
                    Last Uploads
                    Last Pagers
                    Last PWFails
                    Last Carrier

                  The List view gadget beneath the cycle gadget (Listview
                  gadget 2) will then update with a list of the
                  Last <whatever> for that node.  (i.e.  Last Callers)
                  (this list will automatically-update while the node is
                  running)

                  If the node is not started you will get a blank list.

  Information   - Click this button after selecting an item from the listview
                  gadget above this gadget, the control program will then
                  attempt to bring up some relevant information about the item
                  selected.

                  E.G. Say you had Last Callers for node 2 selected,
                  clicked on user called "Hydra", the control program
                  could bring up the information stored in the callers log
                  for the last time that user logged on!

                  Isn't that just so damn usefull ? :-)

                  See BBSGlobal's InformationCMD settings.                      *I*

  Listview 4    - This big listview gadget on the right hand side of the
                  window is basically a replacement for a button bank
                  (ala /X or DOpus).  You can configure the items that appear
                  in this list via the @{"BBSGlobal/ButtonCMD" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/BBSGlobal.guide/ButtonCMD_XX} option            *K*

                  Double clicking on an item in the listview runs the
                  specified program.

                  The advantage over this system compared to a button bank
                  is that you are not limited to how many buttons you can
                  have!

                  (For those of you who do not know what a "Button Bank" is:
                  a button bank is a set of buttons, each button clicked on
                  performs a user configurable command, in this case it runs
                  a program)

  Configure     - This brings up the @{" configuration " link ControlConfigWindow} window

  Shutdown all  - Shuts down all nodes that are have a status of READY

                  (note: this is the same as clicking the Close Gadget!)


@EndNode

@Node ControlConfigWindow "Control Configuration Window"

  Control Configuration Window
  ============================

  On this window you will see the following buttons:

  Screen Mode   - This lets you select if you want to use a named public
                  screen or a new public screen.

  Save          - This saves the position of the control window and the
                  screenmode.

  BBS Config    - This will bring up the @{" BBSGlobal " link HBBS:docs/configuration/bbsglobal.guide/MAIN} file using the editor
                  specified with @{" BBSGlobal/EditorCMD " link HBBS:docs/configuration/bbsglobal.guide/editorcmd}

@EndNode

@Node KeyboardShortcuts "Keyboard Shortcuts"

  Keyboard Shortcuts
  ==================

    @{" Watch Windows " link WatchWindowKeys}

@EndNode

@Node WatchWindowKeys "Watch Window Keyboard Shortcuts"

  Watch Window Keyboard Shortcuts
  ===============================

    When you are looking at a watch window/screen you can press certain keys
    to perform actions, these are the keys you can press and what they do..

    Here's a list of keys you can press wheter a user is online or
    when the system as at the await connect door

    Key           Action
    -----------   ------------------------------------------------------------
    F6          - Run User Account Editor door

    F7          - Close Watch Window

    F8          - Switch Between Watch Window or Watch Screen


    Here's a list of the keys you can press and what they do when there's no
    user online.  (note: these keys are dependant on what Await door you
    have installed)


    Key           Action
    -----------   ------------------------------------------------------------
    F1          - Local Login

    F2          - Initialise Modem

    F3          - Answer Modem Now
                  Use this is there is a call coming and you don't want to
                  wait X amount of rings or if you've been taking voice to
                  a user using the same phone line that your modem is
                  connected to.
                  (he should type ATX1D into his comms program and press
                  return, after you have pressed this key and you have put
                  your handset back on the hook)

    F4          - Display the await screen again.

    F5          - Toggle Modem Debug On/Off

    F7          - Closes the watch window

    F8          - switches the watch window between a window and a screen.

    F9          - Run Terminal Door (Turns watch window/screen into a simple
                  comms program. (Cool Huh ?!)

    F10         - Shutdown Node


    Here's a list of the keys you can press when a user is online.

    Key           Action
    -----------   ------------------------------------------------------------
    F1          - Chat Mode Start/Stop
                  pressing calls the system door "SysopChat".  This displays
                  the "StartChat" screen and puts the BBS in CHAT mode.
                  Both the user and the sysop can type things onto the screen
                  and "Talk" to each other!  to exit chat mode the sysop has
                  to press his F1 key again. (or the user can drop carrier!)

    F6          - Brings up user's account details and lets sysop modify for
                  this call and for subsequest calls (permenant modifications)
                  Note: this calls the AccountEditor with the parameter SYSOP

    Shift + F6  - Bring up user's accouts details and lets sysop modify for
                  the duration of the users call. (temporary modifications)
                  Note: this calls the AccountEditor with the parameter SYSOP

    Shift + F10 - Drop Carrier

@EndNode


@Node NodeGUI "Node Control Window GUI"

  Node Control Window GUI
  =======================

  The node's control window has the following gadgets on it:

  Cycle 1        - use this to select one of the following options

                   Chat ON - The pager will page you.
                   Chat OFF - The pager will NOT page you

  Cycle 2        - Use this to select one of the following option

                   OnHook - Put the modem back on the hook, ready to
                            answer incoming calls
                   OffHook - put the modem off-hook, anyone tring to dial in
                             will get a busy signal.

                   Note: This gadget will appear greyed out if the option
                   @{"NodeLocal/UseDevice" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeGlobal.guide/UseDevice} is set to FALSE

  Cycle 3        - Use this to make a node reserved, select:

                   UnReserved - everyone can login on this node as normal
                   Reserved - only the selected user can login on this node

                   *C* In future, this will support more options.

  Init Modem     - Re-initialise the modem.

                   Note: This gadget will appear greyed out if the option
                   @{"NodeLocal/UseDevice" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeGlobal.guide/UseDevice} is set to FALSE


  Watch          - Clicking this shows or opens the watch window/screen
                   for this node.  The watch window allows you to see what
                   the user is doing.

                   Note: if this does nothing, then you will have HBBS
                   configured to open a screen for the watch window for
                   this node and the screen could not be opened for some reason
                   (Normally caused by you not picking a screen mode)

  Chat           - Opens or brings the watch window/screen to the front
                   and starts the SysopChat door.

  Settings       - Clicking this opens a @{" settings " link NodeSettingsWin} window

  Info           - Clicking this opens the @{" information " link NodeInfoWin }window

@EndNode

@Node NodeInfoWin "Node Information Window"

  Node Information Window
  =======================

  In this window, you will see the following information:

  Calls          - Calls today

  UL             - Files uploaded today

  DL             - Files downloaded today

  Cycle 1        - Lets you select one of the following

                   Callers
                   Uploads
                   Downloads
                   Pagers
                   PW Fails
                   Carrier Losses

                   Selecting one of these makes the listview below
                   display the requested information.

  ListView 1     - Shows whatever is required for Cycle 1's current
                   setting.

@EndNode

@Node NodeSettingsWin "Node Settings Window"

  Node Settings Window
  ====================

  In this window, you will see the following gadgets:

  Screen/Window Settings
  ----------------------

  Screen Mode    - Clicking this lets you select a screen mode
                   for the watch window.

  Cycle 1        - Lets you select

                   Use Screen - If set the watch window will appearon it's own
                                public screen.
                   Use Window - If set the watch window will open on the same
                                screen as the Control program

                   It will default to what ever is set by @{" NodeLocal/UseScreen " link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeGlobal.guide/UseScreen}

  Save Windows   - This button will save the positions of the Node control
                   GUI and the watch window (if it's configured to use a window)

  Modem Settings
  --------------

  Note: These gadgets will appear greyed out if the option @{"NodeLocal/UseDevice" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeGlobal.guide/UseDevice}
  is set to FALSE

  Modem Debug    - Ticking this will enable @{"NodeLocal/ModemDebug" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/Device.guide/ModemDebug} for as long as the
                   node is open or until it is disabled.

  Modem Log      - Ticking this will enable @{"NodeLocal/ModemLog" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/Device.guide/ModemLog} for as long as the
                   node is open or until it is disabled.

  Dump Modem     - Ticking this will enable @{"NodeLocal/DumpModem" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/Device.guide/DeumpModem} for as long as the
                   node is open or until it is disabled.


  Misc Settings
  -------------

  Allow logins   - Unticking this will disallow logins on the node

  CallersLog     - Clicking this will use your text editor to display the
                   callerslog file for this node.

  DoorLog        - Clicking this will use your text editor to display the
                   callerslog file for this node.

  NodeConfig     - Brings up the @{" NodeLocal " link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeLocal.guide/MAIN} config file for this node

  Note: the above options use the @{" BBSGlobal/EditorCMD " link HBBS:docs/configuration/bbsglobal.guide/editorcmd} settings
                   to decide what program to use to edit the files.

@EndNode


